2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a hybrid approach to goal-oriented dialogue generation using neural networks. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed approach uses a neural encoder-decoder architecture. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper incorporates a retrieval step to improve the dialogue generation. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper evaluates the proposed approach using human evaluators to rate the appropriateness and fluency of the generated responses.
